1
00:00:03,296 --> 00:00:05,548
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

2
00:00:05,632 --> 00:00:08,301
<i>I pledged a vow to the revolution</i>

3
00:00:08,384 --> 00:00:13,389
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

4
00:00:13,473 --> 00:00:18,603
<i>I'm going to change</i>

5
00:00:27,028 --> 00:00:31,366
<i>The future that
the forbidden fruit foretells...</i>

6
00:00:31,449 --> 00:00:35,370
<i>I'm going to change</i>

7
00:00:35,453 --> 00:00:39,791
<i>The dream into reality</i>

8
00:00:42,210 --> 00:00:48,216
<i>The ending</i>

9
00:00:48,299 --> 00:00:51,678
<i>That everybody wants</i>

10
00:00:52,595 --> 00:00:54,889
<i>Within the spreading darkness</i>

11
00:00:54,973 --> 00:00:57,642
<i>I pledged our vow to the revolution</i>

12
00:00:57,725 --> 00:01:02,564
<i>I can't let anybody interrupt it</i>

13
00:01:02,689 --> 00:01:07,944
<i>Someday I'll show you</i>

14
00:01:08,027 --> 00:01:11,406
<i>A bright and ideal</i>

15
00:01:11,489 --> 00:01:17,370
<i>World</i>

16
00:01:26,004 --> 00:01:28,965
GLARE

17
00:01:30,717 --> 00:01:34,679
That was footage that was coincidentally
captured on surveillance cameras

18
00:01:34,804 --> 00:01:37,557
of the FBI agents who died in Japan.

19
00:01:39,350 --> 00:01:41,686
Please show me only
the scenes of Raye Penber

20
00:01:41,811 --> 00:01:46,399
passing the ticket gate,
riding the train, and then dying.

21
00:01:46,566 --> 00:01:47,734
Yes.

22
00:01:48,234 --> 00:01:49,277
Let's see...

23
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:50,528
It's right below that.

24
00:01:51,362 --> 00:01:52,405
Oh, this?

25
00:01:53,865 --> 00:01:59,954
Raye Penber enters through the ticket
gate of Shinjuku Station at 15:11.

26
00:02:00,496 --> 00:02:03,416
At 15:13,
he rides the Yamanote Line.

27
00:02:03,708 --> 00:02:07,378
Even if he was following someone,
it would be difficult...

28
00:02:07,503 --> 00:02:10,548
to conclude anything from
this blurry video.

29
00:02:11,049 --> 00:02:13,092
And at 16:42...

30
00:02:14,218 --> 00:02:15,928
Oh, thank you very much.

31
00:02:16,596 --> 00:02:22,143
And at 16:42, he gets off and dies at
the Tokyo Station Platform.

32
00:02:23,353 --> 00:02:24,896
It's strange, isn't it?

33
00:02:26,230 --> 00:02:27,732
What's strange, L?

34
00:02:28,107 --> 00:02:29,609
Did you notice something?

35
00:02:32,195 --> 00:02:33,613
Judging by this footage,

36
00:02:33,905 --> 00:02:36,157
from the time that Raye Penber got
on the train until his death,

37
00:02:36,282 --> 00:02:40,078
he had been riding for an hour and a half.
The Yamanote Line only takes an hour.

38
00:02:40,870 --> 00:02:42,413
That envelope is especially strange.

39
00:02:42,914 --> 00:02:43,956
Envelope?

40
00:02:46,709 --> 00:02:47,919
He's holding that envelope

41
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,921
as he enters the ticket gate
and reaches the platform.

42
00:02:50,546 --> 00:02:51,589
L-indeed.

43
00:02:52,048 --> 00:02:53,132
He's carrying it.
He's carrying it!

44
00:02:53,716 --> 00:02:55,259
But by the time he dies...

45
00:02:56,052 --> 00:02:57,095
It's gone!

46
00:02:57,553 --> 00:02:59,931
Ryuzaki, it's amazing you noticed that!

47
00:03:00,473 --> 00:03:03,434
Envelope isn't on the list of
articles he left behind.

48
00:03:03,768 --> 00:03:06,145
Which means it was left in the train.

49
00:03:06,896 --> 00:03:08,981
And this video of Penber's
final moments...

50
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:12,985
It looks to me as if
he's desperately trying

51
00:03:13,069 --> 00:03:15,279
to look inside the train.

52
00:03:15,822 --> 00:03:17,990
If so, could there be a hint there?

53
00:03:18,616 --> 00:03:20,660
Wouldn't it be interesting
if Kira was there?

54
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:22,120
C-Couldn't be!

55
00:03:22,787 --> 00:03:24,997
I don't think so either.

56
00:03:25,832 --> 00:03:27,709
There's no reason for Kira,
who can control death from a distance,

57
00:03:27,792 --> 00:03:29,335
to come to the scene of the crime.

58
00:03:30,670 --> 00:03:36,509
But despite that, he may
have tried something bold.

59
00:03:44,642 --> 00:03:46,477
Light, are you all right?

60
00:03:46,936 --> 00:03:48,813
You've been writing criminals'
names in the Death Note

61
00:03:48,855 --> 00:03:52,150
for four days already
without sleeping.

62
00:03:52,692 --> 00:03:57,655
Why do you have to set up a death
schedule for several months ahead?

63
00:03:57,989 --> 00:03:59,198
Quite simply...

64
00:03:59,323 --> 00:04:01,159
Suppose I get hospitalized.
People will say that...

65
00:04:01,284 --> 00:04:04,162
"As soon as Chief Yagami's son
was hospitalized,

66
00:04:04,287 --> 00:04:07,373
"criminals have
stopped dying, haven't they?"

67
00:04:07,790 --> 00:04:09,250
So that's why...

68
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:10,668
But are you sure

69
00:04:10,710 --> 00:04:14,172
any date before the end of
their predestined life span is all right?

70
00:04:14,797 --> 00:04:18,843
Shinigami never use it that way,
so I can't say for sure, but...

71
00:04:19,010 --> 00:04:22,221
In theory, any time before
their natural deaths should be all right.

72
00:04:23,973 --> 00:04:25,391
You're not much help.

73
00:04:25,558 --> 00:04:26,684
You can't.

74
00:04:27,351 --> 00:04:28,352
No, I'm not.

75
00:04:29,187 --> 00:04:31,105
Yes, please wait one moment.

76
00:04:31,647 --> 00:04:32,690
Ryuzaki.

77
00:04:32,815 --> 00:04:38,571
Ukita at the NPA has received
a phone call he's concerned about.

78
00:04:38,821 --> 00:04:41,908
Then have him give the telephone
number of number five

79
00:04:41,991 --> 00:04:45,578
and have the informant
call that number.

80
00:04:46,871 --> 00:04:49,749
Matsuda, you can turn on
your cell phone.

81
00:04:49,874 --> 00:04:51,459
I mean, please turn it on.

82
00:04:51,751 --> 00:04:52,794
Oh, yes.

83
00:04:56,839 --> 00:05:00,760
Yes, this is Suzuki, head of the Public Information
Processing Unit for the Kira Case.

84
00:05:02,011 --> 00:05:03,554
Raye Penber's fiancée?

85
00:05:04,388 --> 00:05:07,892
Naomi Misora...
I've heard that name somewhere...

86
00:05:12,063 --> 00:05:16,484
<i>It's her. . .from the Los Angeles
BB murder case...</i>

87
00:05:16,943 --> 00:05:22,073
<i>So that's it... She worked under me on
that case and now she's in Japan.</i>

88
00:05:26,577 --> 00:05:30,331
She's been missing
since the death of her fiance.

89
00:05:30,915 --> 00:05:33,668
Anyone would be depressed
over the death of a fiance...

90
00:05:33,876 --> 00:05:34,961
Could it be...

91
00:05:35,044 --> 00:05:36,128
...suicide?

92
00:05:37,046 --> 00:05:39,757
No, the Naomi Misora I knew

93
00:05:39,799 --> 00:05:42,927
was very strong-willed,
an excellent FBI agent.

94
00:05:43,553 --> 00:05:46,347
She would likely be thinking
of catching Kira.

95
00:05:47,223 --> 00:05:49,141
She was with Penber.

96
00:05:50,059 --> 00:05:51,936
She might have found a clue...

97
00:05:52,812 --> 00:05:55,940
<i>If that's the case,
did Kira get to her first?</i>

98
00:05:58,776 --> 00:06:01,362
Everyone, from now on,
we'll focus our investigation

99
00:06:01,445 --> 00:06:04,323
on the people Raye Penber
was investigating while in Japan.

100
00:06:04,991 --> 00:06:06,450
He was investigating two people

101
00:06:06,492 --> 00:06:08,703
in relation to the police
and the people around them.

102
00:06:09,412 --> 00:06:11,956
Who are they? Who are those two?

103
00:06:12,790 --> 00:06:15,710
Deputy Director General Kitamura
and his family, and...

104
00:06:16,127 --> 00:06:18,170
Detective Superintendent Yagami
and his family.

105
00:06:18,921 --> 00:06:19,964
What?!

106
00:06:20,506 --> 00:06:25,720
I also wish to place wiretaps and
surveillance cameras in both households.

107
00:06:26,929 --> 00:06:31,309
<i>I have to make sure this computer
is clean in case anyone examines it.</i>

108
00:06:34,103 --> 00:06:36,856
<i>I just have to hide a clipping
of the Death Note in here...</i>

109
00:06:39,150 --> 00:06:41,861
You sure are skillful
with your hands.

110
00:06:41,986 --> 00:06:44,071
You're popular with the girls,
aren't you?

111
00:06:44,655 --> 00:06:48,242
That has nothing to do with skill.
It's more about looks than skill.

112
00:06:48,826 --> 00:06:51,162
Ryuk, you aren't popular, are you?

113
00:06:52,830 --> 00:06:54,749
Surveillance cameras? Ryuzaki!

114
00:06:55,041 --> 00:06:57,043
That's way out of the question!

115
00:06:57,668 --> 00:06:59,337
It would become a civil rights issue
if this is discovered...

116
00:06:59,378 --> 00:07:00,880
and we'll all be fired!

117
00:07:01,631 --> 00:07:03,424
Weren't you willing to risk
more than your jobs?

118
00:07:03,507 --> 00:07:05,551
I thought we were
putting our lives on the line.

119
00:07:06,969 --> 00:07:08,054
Ryuzaki...

120
00:07:08,137 --> 00:07:10,431
What is the possibility that
Kira is among them?!

121
00:07:12,016 --> 00:07:15,519
Ten percent...
No, five percent.

122
00:07:16,145 --> 00:07:18,689
No way! All that for only a five-percent
possibility is a bit much.

123
00:07:18,814 --> 00:07:20,900
No... Of the people
we investigated so far...

124
00:07:21,067 --> 00:07:23,694
there wasn't anyone who even
seemed the least bit suspicious.

125
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:25,571
I think we should look into it

126
00:07:25,655 --> 00:07:28,199
even if there's only
a one-percent chance of finding Kira.

127
00:07:28,574 --> 00:07:29,700
Chief!

128
00:07:30,368 --> 00:07:33,871
I never thought that my family
was under suspicion...

129
00:07:34,538 --> 00:07:36,248
Fine.
Please place them!

130
00:07:37,541 --> 00:07:41,420
In return, install them in every part
of the house! Even the bathroom, the toilet!

131
00:07:41,504 --> 00:07:42,880
Don't miss a single corner!

132
00:07:43,506 --> 00:07:44,715
Thank you very much.

133
00:07:45,007 --> 00:07:46,050
That's what I was planning to do.

134
00:07:46,425 --> 00:07:48,594
Chief!
What are you talking about?!

135
00:07:48,761 --> 00:07:52,390
That's right! You have a wife
and daughter, don't you?

136
00:07:52,890 --> 00:07:54,225
I know!

137
00:07:54,725 --> 00:07:57,561
There's no point in doing this
unless we're thorough!

138
00:07:58,020 --> 00:07:59,313
Just be quiet!

139
00:08:02,942 --> 00:08:03,943
Soffy. . -

140
00:08:04,276 --> 00:08:05,611
No, it's okay...

141
00:08:06,362 --> 00:08:07,405
I'm sorry...

142
00:08:09,699 --> 00:08:15,287
Well, out of courtesy, only Yagami and I
will conduct surveillance on his home.

143
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:20,084
Watari, how long will it take to set up
the wiretaps and camera monitors?

144
00:08:20,626 --> 00:08:22,169
Starting tomorrow...

145
00:08:22,378 --> 00:08:26,090
I can set them up at any time once
we know when both families will be out.

146
00:08:29,885 --> 00:08:31,137
See you later, Light.

147
00:08:31,429 --> 00:08:33,097
Yeah, see you tomorrow.

148
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:38,519
<i>What? No one's home yet?</i>

149
00:08:46,944 --> 00:08:47,987
I'm home...

150
00:09:04,962 --> 00:09:07,798
Hey Light, no one seems to be home.

151
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:10,009
Wanna play a game together?
It's been awhile.

152
00:09:11,927 --> 00:09:14,013
Hey Light, let's play a game.

153
00:09:14,930 --> 00:09:15,973
Are you listening to me?

154
00:09:20,519 --> 00:09:21,562
Light?

155
00:09:28,444 --> 00:09:29,820
C-Couldn't be.

156
00:09:30,613 --> 00:09:32,364
I never knew he went to
those lengths!

157
00:09:32,865 --> 00:09:35,659
Could he have something in his
room he doesn't want anyone to see?

158
00:09:36,327 --> 00:09:38,245
If you keep in mind that
he's only seventeen,

159
00:09:38,329 --> 00:09:40,498
there's nothing suspicious
about his behavior.

160
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:43,375
I also did that for no apparent reason.

161
00:09:44,001 --> 00:09:46,045
Have you ever talked to him
about the investigation?

162
00:09:46,295 --> 00:09:47,338
Of course not!

163
00:09:47,379 --> 00:09:50,174
I'd never tell him about anything
classified that hasn't been broadcast.

164
00:09:50,633 --> 00:09:51,592
Besides...

165
00:09:51,675 --> 00:09:53,719
Lately I haven't been returning
home regularly,

166
00:09:53,844 --> 00:09:56,013
and when I do, I'm too tired...
and just go to sleep.

167
00:09:56,847 --> 00:09:57,890
I understand...

168
00:09:59,308 --> 00:10:01,102
Light, where are you going?

169
00:10:03,479 --> 00:10:06,857
Hey, Light, you've been ignoring me!
I'm getting mad.

170
00:10:09,235 --> 00:10:10,528
- There don't seem to be...
- Hey, Light!

171
00:10:10,569 --> 00:10:12,238
Any taps planted on these clothes.

172
00:10:12,488 --> 00:10:13,864
Light...

173
00:10:14,198 --> 00:10:17,409
Ryuk, there's a possibility that there are
wiretaps or surveillance cameras,

174
00:10:17,493 --> 00:10:21,038
no, likely both,
placed within the house.

175
00:10:21,372 --> 00:10:25,042
Huh? But that piece of paper
was still in your door, wasn't it?

176
00:10:25,334 --> 00:10:27,545
That piece of paper was
a fake to make people think

177
00:10:27,670 --> 00:10:30,214
it was there to see whether anyone
had entered the room while I was gone.

178
00:10:30,548 --> 00:10:32,049
The real detector is,
first of all, my door handle.

179
00:10:32,216 --> 00:10:33,217
Door handle?

180
00:10:33,509 --> 00:10:35,386
When that door is closed,

181
00:10:35,427 --> 00:10:37,429
the door knob naturally rises
to a horizontal position.

182
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:38,889
It won't rise any higher.

183
00:10:39,557 --> 00:10:41,725
But whenever I close the door,

184
00:10:41,892 --> 00:10:44,061
I purposefully lower the door knob

185
00:10:44,103 --> 00:10:45,938
to five millimeters below
its highest position.

186
00:10:46,772 --> 00:10:50,234
In other words, when I open the door,
if the knob is all the way up,

187
00:10:50,401 --> 00:10:52,778
chances are that someone
was in my room.

188
00:10:53,529 --> 00:10:56,115
But I can't rely on just that.

189
00:10:56,907 --> 00:10:59,326
So I also put a mechanical
pencil lead in place.

190
00:10:59,702 --> 00:11:01,287
A pencil lead?

191
00:11:01,704 --> 00:11:02,746
On the hinge.

192
00:11:03,038 --> 00:11:04,123
After I close the door,

193
00:11:04,206 --> 00:11:07,334
I place a mechanical pencil lead
on the hinge at an angle

194
00:11:07,418 --> 00:11:09,503
so that it will break
if the door is opened.

195
00:11:10,212 --> 00:11:12,423
The lead is sure to break
if the door is opened.

196
00:11:13,215 --> 00:11:14,925
I've always taken it out myself
when I entered,

197
00:11:14,967 --> 00:11:16,468
but today, it was broken.

198
00:11:16,719 --> 00:11:19,096
Oh, that. I remember you doing that.

199
00:11:19,388 --> 00:11:20,806
The door handle and the pencil lead.

200
00:11:20,931 --> 00:11:23,267
I have no doubt that someone went in.

201
00:11:23,601 --> 00:11:24,852
Isn't it probably your parents?

202
00:11:25,436 --> 00:11:27,813
My parents and sister probably
wouldn't notice the piece of paper.

203
00:11:28,272 --> 00:11:31,442
It's suspicious because someone
took the time to put it back.

204
00:11:32,443 --> 00:11:33,611
Welcome.

205
00:11:34,278 --> 00:11:38,991
Are you planning to buy a book
to research wiretaps and surveillance?

206
00:11:41,285 --> 00:11:43,787
Ryuk, by the way,
what will happen to your apples?

207
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:45,623
Apples?

208
00:11:46,081 --> 00:11:49,168
Oh! From the surveillance camera...

209
00:11:49,793 --> 00:11:52,296
if I put the apple in my mouth
no one can see it,

210
00:11:52,421 --> 00:11:54,673
but it'll look like it's floating in air
if I'm just holding it.

211
00:11:54,757 --> 00:11:55,841
I thought so...

212
00:11:56,258 --> 00:11:58,552
Shinigami cannot die,
so they won't starve either.

213
00:11:59,094 --> 00:12:01,639
In other words, there's no problem
if I don't give you any apples.

214
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:04,183
Whoa, waitjust a minute, Light!

215
00:12:04,266 --> 00:12:06,143
Apples are to me...

216
00:12:06,936 --> 00:12:10,522
W-Well. .. What cigarettes and liquor
are to humans.

217
00:12:10,773 --> 00:12:12,983
I'll get withdrawal symptoms
if I don't have any for a while...

218
00:12:13,275 --> 00:12:15,027
What kind of symptoms?

219
00:12:15,527 --> 00:12:18,822
My body twists around wildly,
and I'll do handstands.

220
00:12:19,156 --> 00:12:20,199
I don't want to see that...

221
00:12:20,324 --> 00:12:21,325
Right?

222
00:12:21,951 --> 00:12:22,993
Ryuk, listen.

223
00:12:23,369 --> 00:12:28,332
I've given L the hint that
Shinigami love apples.

224
00:12:28,499 --> 00:12:29,667
When did you...

225
00:12:30,459 --> 00:12:32,503
If you really want to eat apples...

226
00:12:34,797 --> 00:12:37,383
find out where all the cameras are.

227
00:12:37,675 --> 00:12:41,095
There might be a place where
you can eat apples without being seen.

228
00:12:42,805 --> 00:12:44,223
All right, Ryuk, let's go!

229
00:12:45,015 --> 00:12:47,226
Yeah!
Finding cameras.

230
00:12:48,185 --> 00:12:50,020
This is also interesting!

231
00:13:10,249 --> 00:13:13,836
Oh right, I have to find cameras...

232
00:13:14,211 --> 00:13:17,089
I can't believe my diligent son
is looking at a magazine like that!

233
00:13:18,215 --> 00:13:19,842
It's normal for a 17-year-old.

234
00:13:20,676 --> 00:13:24,430
But to me, it seems like
he's making an excuse, as if to say,

235
00:13:24,513 --> 00:13:26,682
"I was checking to see
if someone was in this room...

236
00:13:26,765 --> 00:13:29,268
"because I have magazines like these."

237
00:13:30,185 --> 00:13:33,981
Ryuzaki, are you telling me that
you suspect my son?

238
00:13:34,606 --> 00:13:35,691
I do suspect him.

239
00:13:36,275 --> 00:13:38,110
That's why I placed wiretaps
and cameras in your house

240
00:13:38,193 --> 00:13:40,321
as well as
the Deputy Director General's house.

241
00:13:42,781 --> 00:13:44,992
I found a camera in the air conditioner.

242
00:13:46,327 --> 00:13:48,329
<i>So there were cameras...</i>

243
00:13:49,038 --> 00:13:50,998
<i>That probably means
there are wire taps as well.</i>

244
00:13:51,165 --> 00:13:52,916
<i>Even if this is for the Kira case,</i>

245
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:56,211
<i>I can't believe the Japanese police
would go this far.</i>

246
00:13:57,004 --> 00:13:58,172
<i>This is L's doing...</i>

247
00:13:58,839 --> 00:14:00,966
<i>If that's the case,
how far has he narrowed it down to?</i>

248
00:14:01,633 --> 00:14:03,385
<i>He must be down to at least someone</i>

249
00:14:03,469 --> 00:14:07,848
<i>that Raye Penber was investigating
or he would have never gone this far.</i>

250
00:14:10,142 --> 00:14:11,810
<i>Tricked by the cover again!</i>

251
00:14:12,478 --> 00:14:14,146
<i>No, in this case, I should act as if...</i>

252
00:14:14,229 --> 00:14:17,900
<i>I was the only one being suspected
and being watched.</i>

253
00:14:19,318 --> 00:14:20,402
<i>It'll be all right.</i>

254
00:14:20,486 --> 00:14:22,738
<i>I've been preparing for
something like this...</i>

255
00:14:22,821 --> 00:14:24,365
<i>That's why I got
these magazines.</i>

256
00:14:28,327 --> 00:14:29,370
Light...

257
00:14:30,371 --> 00:14:34,875
It's time for dinner...

258
00:14:36,502 --> 00:14:37,503
<i>I...</i>

259
00:14:38,420 --> 00:14:39,463
<i>love you.</i>

260
00:14:45,177 --> 00:14:47,346
Hideki Ryuga, you're so dreamy!

261
00:14:47,471 --> 00:14:50,724
There's nobody in my class like him!
No one at all!

262
00:14:50,808 --> 00:14:51,809
Sayu...

263
00:14:51,892 --> 00:14:53,352
Eat your dinner.

264
00:14:53,727 --> 00:14:54,770
I will later!

265
00:14:55,270 --> 00:14:58,399
Mr. Aizawa, are the Kitamuras
watching television now?

266
00:14:58,774 --> 00:14:59,775
<i>Yes.</i>

267
00:14:59,900 --> 00:15:01,151
Aside from the Deputy Director General,

268
00:15:01,235 --> 00:15:02,861
the four of them are watching
television as they eat.

269
00:15:03,278 --> 00:15:04,363
It's channel four.

270
00:15:05,531 --> 00:15:09,451
Watari, order the various television
companies to broadcast our banner.

271
00:15:09,868 --> 00:15:10,953
Understood.

272
00:15:11,370 --> 00:15:12,329
NKK NEWS FLASH

273
00:15:12,413 --> 00:15:14,206
Huh? What?

274
00:15:15,124 --> 00:15:17,418
"In response to the Kira murders,

275
00:15:17,543 --> 00:15:22,798
"the ICPO has decided to dispatch
1,500 investigators

276
00:15:22,881 --> 00:15:26,927
"from various developed
countries to Japan."

277
00:15:28,011 --> 00:15:29,430
1,500 investigators?

278
00:15:29,888 --> 00:15:30,931
Wow!

279
00:15:31,723 --> 00:15:34,393
<i>There should also be cameras
in the living room.</i>

280
00:15:34,726 --> 00:15:37,146
<i>Whether this news is real or not,</i>

281
00:15:37,646 --> 00:15:39,857
<i>it's being shown to me
to get some kind of reaction...</i>

282
00:15:41,024 --> 00:15:44,194
<i>L... It's the same trick you
used the first time.</i>

283
00:15:45,237 --> 00:15:46,780
The ICPO sure is stupid.

284
00:15:48,740 --> 00:15:50,784
There's no point in making
this announcement.

285
00:15:50,909 --> 00:15:52,661
If they're going to send them in,

286
00:15:52,744 --> 00:15:54,788
they should let them come in
and investigate in secret.

287
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:58,417
<i>Even those FBI agents investigating
in secret were killed.</i>

288
00:15:58,959 --> 00:16:00,502
<i>The outcome will be the same.</i>

289
00:16:01,295 --> 00:16:06,300
<i>This is just an overblown attempt
to shock Kira into exposing himself.</i>

290
00:16:07,050 --> 00:16:09,636
<i>But, it just might be completely
obvious to Kira.</i>

291
00:16:12,848 --> 00:16:14,766
Your son is very smart.

292
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:17,186
Huh? Yeah, well...

293
00:16:17,269 --> 00:16:18,353
<i>Thanks for dinner.</i>

294
00:16:19,146 --> 00:16:22,191
No way! Are you eating potato chips
after dinner?

295
00:16:22,316 --> 00:16:24,651
You look so fit right now...
do you wanna get fat?

296
00:16:24,943 --> 00:16:26,820
It's just a late night snack
while I study for exams.

297
00:16:30,491 --> 00:16:31,992
L-Light...

298
00:16:32,576 --> 00:16:34,870
I found all of the cameras...

299
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:37,915
I guess even Shinigami get tired
when they try hard...

300
00:16:38,457 --> 00:16:40,083
I'll explain now.

301
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:43,504
It's a bit complex, so pay attention.

302
00:16:43,962 --> 00:16:46,507
I don't want to explain it again.

303
00:16:46,673 --> 00:16:48,717
All right, time to study hard!

304
00:16:49,801 --> 00:16:52,012
There are so many cameras.

305
00:16:52,554 --> 00:16:56,183
Whoever put them here must've
expected you to find some.

306
00:16:56,642 --> 00:16:58,185
There are 64 in all.

307
00:16:58,644 --> 00:17:00,062
<i>It's definitely L.</i>

308
00:17:00,812 --> 00:17:03,273
<i>He had no qualms putting
a death row inmate in his place</i>

309
00:17:03,357 --> 00:17:04,691
<i>when he challenged me.</i>

310
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:07,528
<i>He knows no limits...</i>

311
00:17:07,819 --> 00:17:11,281
So where am I going to eat
apples in this situation?

312
00:17:11,573 --> 00:17:13,825
<i>Obviously that's impossible, Ryuk.</i>

313
00:17:13,951 --> 00:17:17,120
Oh, yeah you can't talk to
me in this house, can you?

314
00:17:17,538 --> 00:17:19,706
Tomorrow, tell me when
we go outside.

315
00:17:20,165 --> 00:17:22,751
Okay, I got this one right.

316
00:17:23,502 --> 00:17:25,837
<i>Judging from the number of cameras,</i>

317
00:17:25,921 --> 00:17:28,423
<i>he's planning on making
his decision in a short amount of time...</i>

318
00:17:28,966 --> 00:17:32,052
<i>A normal person would
probably give himself away, but...</i>

319
00:17:32,803 --> 00:17:34,555
<i>you're messing with
the wrong person, L...</i>

320
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:35,722
<i>this is as far as you'll get.</i>

321
00:17:51,363 --> 00:17:52,990
<i>I've written down criminals
in the Death Note.</i>

322
00:17:53,073 --> 00:17:55,450
<i>So they will continue to die
over the next three weeks, but...</i>

323
00:17:56,034 --> 00:17:59,830
<i>Kira has already shown L that
he can control the time of death.</i>

324
00:18:00,330 --> 00:18:01,498
<i>So in this case...</i>

325
00:18:01,832 --> 00:18:04,209
<i>Current criminals being
broadcast on the news...</i>

326
00:18:04,418 --> 00:18:07,838
<i>have to die while I'm not
receiving any knowledge of them.</i>

327
00:18:08,463 --> 00:18:09,506
Oh no!

328
00:18:09,631 --> 00:18:11,091
My withdrawal symptoms!

329
00:18:12,009 --> 00:18:13,677
<i>Just watch, L!</i>

330
00:18:19,391 --> 00:18:21,893
<i>With Ryuk's information
and my prior preparations,</i>

331
00:18:21,977 --> 00:18:24,980
<i>I can kill criminals
currently being broadcast</i>

332
00:18:25,063 --> 00:18:31,278
<i>while masquerading...
as a regular high school student.</i>

333
00:18:32,029 --> 00:18:34,114
<i>I'll solve equations
with my right hand...</i>

334
00:18:35,032 --> 00:18:36,658
<i>and write names with my left.</i>

335
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:39,161
SUSPECT: TAYOSHI MURAO

336
00:18:40,746 --> 00:18:43,373
<i>Grab a potato chip...
And eat it!</i>

337
00:18:54,426 --> 00:18:56,637
After dinner, your son has
continued studying

338
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:59,056
without turning on
a television or computer, hasn't he?

339
00:18:59,723 --> 00:19:02,434
It's because the Entrance Exams
are less than ten days away...

340
00:19:12,194 --> 00:19:14,196
<i>Now a criminal which I should
have no knowledge about...</i>

341
00:19:14,279 --> 00:19:16,698
<i>will die of a heart attack
in forty seconds.</i>

342
00:19:18,116 --> 00:19:21,244
<i>The witness to my alibi is L himself.</i>

343
00:19:27,376 --> 00:19:29,127
All right, just a little more!

344
00:19:35,258 --> 00:19:36,259
Ryuzaki.

345
00:19:36,635 --> 00:19:37,761
Watari, what is it?

346
00:19:38,470 --> 00:19:41,807
Two people just broadcast on
today's nine o'clock news,

347
00:19:41,890 --> 00:19:45,018
a bank clerk on suspicion of
embezzlement during questioning...

348
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:48,188
And a purse snatcher
in a detention center...

349
00:19:48,438 --> 00:19:50,982
just died of heart attacks.

350
00:19:51,441 --> 00:19:52,401
It's Kira!

351
00:19:52,776 --> 00:19:54,653
During that time in your home...

352
00:19:54,778 --> 00:19:57,447
your wife and daughter were
watching a drama.

353
00:19:58,073 --> 00:19:59,241
As soon as that was finished,

354
00:19:59,324 --> 00:20:01,868
they turned off the television
and didn't watch anything aften/vards.

355
00:20:02,828 --> 00:20:05,372
From just past 7:30 until now,
11 o'clock,

356
00:20:05,455 --> 00:20:07,207
the only thing your son has
done is study.

357
00:20:07,791 --> 00:20:10,794
Kira needs a face
and a name to kill...

358
00:20:11,503 --> 00:20:15,298
Those who did not watch
the news, can't be Kira, huh?

359
00:20:16,091 --> 00:20:18,593
This means my family is innocent, right?

360
00:20:19,428 --> 00:20:24,558
Kira killed people with minor crimes as
soon as they were broadcast, didn't he?

361
00:20:26,351 --> 00:20:28,812
Even if it is the first day
the cameras were installed,

362
00:20:29,062 --> 00:20:31,690
the Yagami household is
so clean, it's almost funny.

363
00:20:36,445 --> 00:20:38,655
Light, are you awake?

364
00:20:39,489 --> 00:20:41,158
Yeah, I'm up.

365
00:20:41,742 --> 00:20:44,745
Today is trash day, so bring out
any garbage if you have any.

366
00:20:45,537 --> 00:20:47,080
What a pain!

367
00:20:47,247 --> 00:20:48,665
What are you talking about?

368
00:20:49,166 --> 00:20:52,335
I always say you should be doing
this without me reminding you!

369
00:20:52,711 --> 00:20:53,879
Yeah yeah...

370
00:20:58,383 --> 00:20:59,968
The weather today is nice.

371
00:21:00,844 --> 00:21:04,431
Well... I don't know if you'll do
just about anything if it's for yourself

372
00:21:04,514 --> 00:21:06,266
or if you're just a big spender, but...

373
00:21:06,558 --> 00:21:10,645
didn't that mini-LCD TV
cost 39,800 yen?

374
00:21:13,565 --> 00:21:14,941
Good morning.

375
00:21:23,366 --> 00:21:26,077
TO BE CONTINUED

376
00:21:26,495 --> 00:21:31,416
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

377
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:36,880
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

378
00:21:37,047 --> 00:21:45,889
<i>I'm holding these feelings
that I can't give up in my heart</i>

379
00:21:45,972 --> 00:21:52,229
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

380
00:21:52,312 --> 00:21:56,858
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

381
00:21:57,567 --> 00:22:02,447
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

382
00:22:02,739 --> 00:22:06,243
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

383
00:22:06,368 --> 00:22:09,955
<i>To accomplish</i>

384
00:22:10,539 --> 00:22:15,126
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

385
00:22:15,335 --> 00:22:20,799
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

386
00:22:20,882 --> 00:22:25,929
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

387
00:22:26,388 --> 00:22:31,768
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

388
00:22:36,231 --> 00:22:38,149
PREVIEW

389
00:22:38,233 --> 00:22:40,861
TO-OH UNIVERSITY ENTRANCE CEREMONY

390
00:22:40,861 --> 00:22:42,487
This is perfect.
There's nothing to worry about.

391
00:22:42,571 --> 00:22:45,448
This just proves that
they don't have anything on me.

392
00:22:45,740 --> 00:22:49,703
It's just a contest
between L and me, a match of wits.

393
00:22:49,703 --> 00:22:51,121
NEXT EPISODE: ENCOUNTER

